24:09.960 --> 24:12.440
Jack Chalker's reputation was greatly enhanced

24:12.440 --> 24:14.960
by the popular Well World series of novels.

24:15.300 --> 24:16.980
Now he's at work on a new series,

24:17.180 --> 24:18.840
one which will have four books in it,

24:19.060 --> 24:20.500
entitled The Four Lords of the Diamond.

24:20.980 --> 24:23.040
Two novels have been published so far.

24:23.240 --> 24:26.080
The first is called Lilith, and the second Cerberus.

24:26.760 --> 24:28.280
Chalker comments on the story.

24:29.960 --> 24:35.720
It has a tremendous number of the elements that I have become known for.

24:35.720 --> 24:38.060
It has a lot of new material as well.

24:38.060 --> 24:39.820
It has a lot of political commentary.

24:40.360 --> 24:42.600
It has a lot of social commentary in it.

24:42.840 --> 24:51.920
It is also slam-bang action, Machiavellian intrigue, and everything else, because nobody's going to read your message if you don't entertain first.

24:53.340 --> 24:56.240
As Chalker says, the books have a lot of excitement in them.

24:56.420 --> 24:58.040
In the opening pages of Lilith,

24:58.140 --> 24:59.180
the first book in the series,

24:59.420 --> 25:01.540
a tremendously powerful alien robot

25:01.540 --> 25:04.460
penetrates a top-secret military installation on Earth.

25:04.640 --> 25:09.440
The robot's discovered, but he escapes and heads for a planetary system called the Warden Diamond.

25:09.820 --> 25:11.680
The Earth government sends its top agent.

25:13.500 --> 25:28.200
These are four worlds in one system that are basically a prison planet series, and you get dropped on there, and the foundation idea, which appeals to me an awful lot,

25:28.360 --> 25:37.060
is an alien race discovers us before we discover them decides that it can't win a war against us.

25:37.420 --> 25:44.500
Maybe they're, you know, there's just not as many of them, or there's technological problems or something like that.

25:45.000 --> 25:53.060
So they study us and study us, and they discover that, as in all human societies, there is this massive criminal syndicate,

25:54.060 --> 26:07.520
and that this criminal syndicate, leaders are mostly imprisoned for life on the four lords of the, well, the diamond, the Warden Diamond, these four worlds.

26:09.620 --> 26:18.820
So what the aliens do is they contact these bitter super crooks, and they take out a contract on human civilization.

26:20.560 --> 26:24.100
The agent can't land on any of the four worlds of the Warden Diamond.

26:24.460 --> 26:28.980
A tiny organism on these worlds enters the body and makes a person a virtual prisoner.

26:29.320 --> 26:29.720
Right.

26:29.920 --> 26:34.020
If you try to leave, you die a painful death. There seems to be no cure for it either.

26:34.020 --> 26:41.600
So what the agent does is have his personality implanted into four separate bodies, and these bodies are sent to each of the worlds.

26:41.800 --> 26:45.700
And he monitors what is happening through a computer hookup orbiting the Warden system.

26:46.860 --> 26:59.300
Part of what the book is about is that we have a sort of surrogate him down on each of these worlds who starts off pretty much almost identical to him.

27:00.100 --> 27:05.180
And he's following this whole thing with his whole system of values, beliefs, and so on.

27:05.520 --> 27:10.980
And he's watching the surrogates change into quite different people.

27:12.020 --> 27:17.540
And it begins to eat away at his own sense of values, his own sense of duty.

27:18.200 --> 27:28.600
As a matter of fact, in the third book, he begins to realize that the people who sent him there on this mission anticipated this.

27:29.020 --> 27:37.660
And that his computer detective aide who he has dialogues with and discusses everything with may be more than that.

27:37.840 --> 27:39.420
It may be something of a watchdog.

27:41.420 --> 27:48.580
Chalker promises an exciting ending when the agent struggles with his own newly discovered values, with the computer, and with the aliens.

27:50.240 --> 27:51.760
I don't like cop-outs.

27:51.980 --> 27:54.500
I don't like stringing people along and then not delivering.

27:54.960 --> 28:02.020
So, um, you will get, you will get real, I don't know whether you can say flesh and blood, but something.

28:02.920 --> 28:13.580
Aliens. And, uh, whatever they're made of, uh, you will meet the aliens, you will, uh, have a face down, and the solution to the whole thing

28:13.580 --> 28:19.540
and exactly what's going on is, uh, uh, quite bizarre, and I don't think anybody's going to figure it out.

